{"type":"message","id":"11387e98","parentId":"daddb389","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:46:47.532Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_q7bajfk8lfvu_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4850\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3299\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\n[mutation proposed] a\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 034616 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":32427,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4850\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3299\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\n[mutation proposed] a\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 034616 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774338407531}}
{"type":"message","id":"c80097b1","parentId":"11387e98","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:46:47.535Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_q7bajfk8lfvu_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 034415\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\n\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- There's pending work on TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n- Next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe most recent pulse was pulse_2026-03-24 034314.md\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take to advance the TIC experiment. I should:\r\n\r\n1. First understand what pulse logs exist\r\n2. Implement a TIC classifier that can:\r\n   - Identify invariants vs variants in pulse content\r\n   - Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n   - Measure accuracy against success criteria\r\n\r\nA concrete file edit could be:\r\n- Creating a new script for TIC analysis\r\n- Creating the TIC experiment specification\r\n- Starting to implement the classifier\r\n\r\nLet me look at what would be most useful. Since I need to implement TIC, I could:\r\n1. Create a script that analyzes pulse logs for invariants\r\n2. Create a specification document for the TIC experiment\r\n3. Modify the pulse script to include TIC classification\r\n\r\nGiven that I need to advance the TIC experiment, creating an initial TIC classifier script seems like a good concrete action. Let me create `src/tic_classifier.py` or similar.\r\n\r\nActually, let me think more carefully. The most impactful action would be to:\r\n1. Create the TIC implementation that can analyze pulse logs\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that implements the TIC classifier. This would:\r\n- Load recent pulse logs\r\n- Identify invariant patterns (things that persist across pulses)\r\n- Identify variant patterns (things that change)\r\n- Measure classification accuracy\r\n- Attempt next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete file edit that advances the stated next action.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires a classifier to analyze pulse logs. I have 7 pulse log files in `logs/` that can be used to identify invariants vs variants and test prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `src/tic_classifier.py` - a Python script implementing the TIC classifier that analyzes pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns and tests next-pulse prediction against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\nSuccess criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nimport json\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nINVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"Phase \\d+\",\r\n    r\"goals?:\",\r\n    r\"Pending:\",\r\n    r\"Active\",\r\n    r\"Completed\",\r\n    r\"research/\",\r\n    r\"\\.md\",\r\n]\r\nVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\",\r\n    r\"\\d{6}\",\r\n    r\"Last updated:\",\r\n    r\"Last pulse:\",\r\n    r\"SUCCESS|FAILURE|ERROR\",\r\n]\r\n\r\ndef load_pulses(n=7):\r\n    \"\"\"Load last n pulse logs sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n    files = sorted(LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=os.path.getmtime, reverse=True)\r\n    return [f.read_text() for f in files[:n]]\r\n\r\ndef extract_features(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract features for classification.\"\"\"\r\n    features = {\r\n        \"has_goals\": bool(re.search(r\"## (Goals|Current|Pending)\", text)),\r\n        \"has_mutations\": bool(re.search(r\"### MUTATION\", text, re.IGNORECASE)),\r\n        \"has_observation\": bool(re.search(r\"### OBSERVATION\", text, re.IGNORECASE)),\r\n        \"has_action\": bool(re.search(r\"### ACTION\", text, re.IGNORECASE)),\r\n        \"phase_refs\": len(re.findall(r\"Phase \\d+\", text)),\r\n        \"doc_refs\": len(re.findall(r\"research/[\\w-]+\\.md\", text)),\r\n        \"timestamp_density\": len(re.findall(r\"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\", text)),\r\n    }\r\n    return features\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify text segments as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    invariants = []\r\n    variants = []\r\n    \r\n    for pattern in INVARIANT_PATTERNS:\r\n        invariants.extend(re.findall(pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE))\r\n    for pattern in VARIANT_PATTERNS:\r\n        variants.extend(re.findall(pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE))\r\n    \r\n    return {\"invariants\": len(invariants), \"variants\": len(variants)}\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse from invariants in recent pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    if len(pulses) < 2:\r\n        return None\r\n    \r\n    invariant_features = Counter()\r\n    for p in pulses[:-1]:\r\n        feats = extract_features(p)\r\n        for k, v in feats.items():\r\n            if v > 0:\r\n                invariant_features[k] += v\r\n    \r\n    predicted = {k: v > (len(pulses) - 1) * 0.5 for k, v in invariant_features.items()}\r\n    return predicted\r\n\r\ndef evaluate_tic():\r\n    \"\"\"Run TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    pulses = load_pulses(7)\r\n    results = {\"classification\": [], \"prediction\": [], \"accuracy\": {}}\r\n    \r\n    for i, pulse in enumerate(pulses):\r\n        classified = classify_content(pulse)\r\n        results[\"classification\"].append(classified)\r\n    \r\n    # Test next-pulse prediction\r\n    correct = 0\r\n    total = 0\r\n    for\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:44:53"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1305,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 034415\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\n\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- There's pending work on TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n- Next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe most recent pulse was pulse_2026-03-24 034314.md\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take to advance the TIC experiment. I should:\r\n\r\n1. First understand what pulse logs exist\r\n2. Implement a TIC classifier that can:\r\n   - Identify invariants vs variants in pulse content\r\n   - Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n   - Measure accuracy against success criteria\r\n\r\nA concrete file edit could be:\r\n- Creating a new script for TIC analysis\r\n- Creating the TIC experiment specification\r\n- Starting to implement the classifier\r\n\r\nLet me look at what would be most useful. Since I need to implement TIC, I could:\r\n1. Create a script that analyzes pulse logs for invariants\r\n2. Create a specification document for the TIC experiment\r\n3. Modify the pulse script to include TIC classification\r\n\r\nGiven that I need to advance the TIC experiment, creating an initial TIC classifier script seems like a good concrete action. Let me create `src/tic_classifier.py` or similar.\r\n\r\nActually, let me think more carefully. The most impactful action would be to:\r\n1. Create the TIC implementation that can analyze pulse logs\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that implements the TIC classifier. This would:\r\n- Load recent pulse logs\r\n- Identify invariant patterns (things that persist across pulses)\r\n- Identify variant patterns (things that change)\r\n- Measure classification accuracy\r\n- Attempt next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete file edit that advances the stated next action.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires a classifier to analyze pulse logs. I have 7 pulse log files in `logs/` that can be used to identify invariants vs variants and test prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `src/tic_classifier.py` - a Python script implementing the TIC classifier that analyzes pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns and tests next-pulse prediction against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\nSuccess criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nimport json\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nINVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"Phase \\d+\",\r\n    r\"goals?:\",\r\n    r\"Pending:\",\r\n    r\"Active\",\r\n    r\"Completed\",\r\n    r\"research/\",\r\n    r\"\\.md\",\r\n]\r\nVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\",\r\n    r\"\\d{6}\",\r\n    r\"Last updated:\",\r\n    r\"Last pulse:\",\r\n    r\"SUCCESS|FAILURE|ERROR\",\r\n]\r\n\r\ndef load_pulses(n=7):\r\n    \"\"\"Load last n pulse logs sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n    files = sorted(LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=os.path.getmtime, reverse=True)\r\n    return [f.read_text() for f in files[:n]]\r\n\r\ndef extract_features(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract features for classification.\"\"\"\r\n    features = {\r\n        \"has_goals\": bool(re.search(r\"## (Goals|Current|Pending)\", text)),\r\n        \"has_mutations\": bool(re.search(r\"### MUTATION\", text, re.IGNORECASE)),\r\n        \"has_observation\": bool(re.search(r\"### OBSERVATION\", text, re.IGNORECASE)),\r\n        \"has_action\": bool(re.search(r\"### ACTION\", text, re.IGNORECASE)),\r\n        \"phase_refs\": len(re.findall(r\"Phase \\d+\", text)),\r\n        \"doc_refs\": len(re.findall(r\"research/[\\w-]+\\.md\", text)),\r\n        \"timestamp_density\": len(re.findall(r\"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\", text)),\r\n    }\r\n    return features\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify text segments as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    invariants = []\r\n    variants = []\r\n    \r\n    for pattern in INVARIANT_PATTERNS:\r\n        invariants.extend(re.findall(pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE))\r\n    for pattern in VARIANT_PATTERNS:\r\n        variants.extend(re.findall(pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE))\r\n    \r\n    return {\"invariants\": len(invariants), \"variants\": len(variants)}\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse from invariants in recent pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    if len(pulses) < 2:\r\n        return None\r\n    \r\n    invariant_features = Counter()\r\n    for p in pulses[:-1]:\r\n        feats = extract_features(p)\r\n        for k, v in feats.items():\r\n            if v > 0:\r\n                invariant_features[k] += v\r\n    \r\n    predicted = {k: v > (len(pulses) - 1) * 0.5 for k, v in invariant_features.items()}\r\n    return predicted\r\n\r\ndef evaluate_tic():\r\n    \"\"\"Run TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    pulses = load_pulses(7)\r\n    results = {\"classification\": [], \"prediction\": [], \"accuracy\": {}}\r\n    \r\n    for i, pulse in enumerate(pulses):\r\n        classified = classify_content(pulse)\r\n        results[\"classification\"].append(classified)\r\n    \r\n    # Test next-pulse prediction\r\n    correct = 0\r\n    total = 0\r\n    for\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:44:53","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774338407532}}
